Upstream bug: the `settings` IPC target's set(key, value) handler assigns
SettingsData[key] directly and calls saveSettings() itself, bypassing
SettingsData.set() (the reactive wrapper around settings/SettingsSpec.js's
Spec.set, which also calls saveSettings() -- so this is a straight swap, not
an addition). That wrapper is what dispatches SPEC[key].onChange hooks, e.g.
currentThemeName -> applyStoredTheme -> Theme.switchTheme. Net effect without
this patch: `dms ipc call settings set currentThemeName custom` persists the
value to settings.json and the live SettingsData property, but the rendered
theme never updates until the shell process restarts or the user reselects a
theme through the Settings UI -- a silent dead switch for any external
automation driving theme selection over IPC. Verified against
AvengeMedia/DankMaterialShell@74896fb87cb9e4bb866dbabcfd754e3e649ad0c7.
--- a/DMSShellIPC.qml
+++ b/DMSShellIPC.qml
@@ -1045,8 +1045,7 @@
                 }
 
                 log.warn("Setting:", key, value);
-                SettingsData[key] = value;
-                SettingsData.saveSettings();
+                SettingsData.set(key, value);
                 return "SETTINGS_SET_SUCCESS";
             } catch (e) {
                 log.warn("Failed to set property:", key, "error:", e);
